    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using the `bufhidden = \"delete\"` option in terminal buffers, the buffer gets correctly deleted when closed, but not when another buffer replaces it in its window.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open Neovim: `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Open a terminal buffer: `:terminal ls`\r\n3. Set option: `:set bufhidden=delete`\r\n4. Open new buffer in current window: `:enew`\r\n5. Look at buffer list: `:ls`\r\n\r\nYou still see the terminal buffer in the buffer list but it should have been deleted.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nYou can see that `bufhidden = delete` does correctly delete the terminal buffer if you close its window along with the terminal buffer:\r\n\r\n1. Open neovim: `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Create a split: `:split`\r\n3. Open a terminal buffer: `:terminal ls`\r\n4. Set option: `:set bufhidden=delete`\r\n5. Close split: `:q`\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim always closes terminal buffers of finished commands when the buffers are hidden.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 37\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
